Print results from owl fit

Source: R/print.R
print.Owl.Rd

Print results from owl fit

# S3 method for Owl
print(x, ...)

# S3 method for TrainedOwl
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

an object of class 'Owl' or 'TrainedOwl'
...

other arguments passed to print()

Value

Prints output on the screen

Examples

fit <- owl(wine$x, wine$y, family = "multinomial")
print(fit, digits = 1)
